---
description: Infrastructure repository rules
globs: SolarTracker.Infrastructure/Repositories/**/*.cs
alwaysApply: false
---

# Infrastructure Repositories

- Each entity has its own concrete repository.
- Repositories implement write operations only.
- Allowed repository methods are `AddAsync`, `UpdateAsync`, and `DeleteAsync`.

# Implementation Rules

- Repository functionality must be implemented directly inside the concrete repository.
- Do not introduce shared generic CRUD helper classes unless a dedicated rule explicitly allows them.
- Use entity-specific persistence mappings.
- Persist changes explicitly in each repository method.

# Forbidden Patterns

- Repositories must not expose `GetByIdAsync`, `ListAsync`, or `AnalyzeAsync`.
- Repositories must not contain business rules.
- Repositories must not return database entities outside `SolarTracker.Infrastructure`.
